## 📦 Installation

### Using npm (Recommended)
```bash
npm install whouser
```

### Using CDN (ES Modules)
```html
<script type="importmap">
{
  "imports": {
    "whouser": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/whouser@latest/src/index.js"
  }
}
</script>
```

---

## 🔧 Quick Start

Get a fingerprint in just one line:

```javascript
import { getFingerprint } from 'whouser';

// Async/Await
const result = await getFingerprint();

console.log(result.hash);
// Output: "a3f5b2-9d4c7e-1f8a3d"

console.log(result.parts);
/*
{
  hardware: "a3f5b2",   // Stable: GPU, CPU, RAM
  software: "9d4c7e",   // Semi-stable: OS, Browser, Locale
  visual: "1f8a3d"      // Volatile: Screen, Fonts, Canvas
}
*/
```

---

## 🧠 Advanced Usage

### 1. High Accuracy Mode
Enable all performance benchmarks (CPU, Memory, WebGL Stress) for maximum differentiation.

```javascript
import { Fingerprint } from 'whouser';

const fp = new Fingerprint({ accuracy: 'high' });
const user = await fp.getFingerprint();
```

### 2. Comparing Two Visitors (Fuzzy Matching)
Check if two hashes belong to the same person, even after a screen resize:

```javascript
const fp = new Fingerprint({ fuzzyThreshold: 0.7 }); // 0.7 = 70% similarity

// Session A
const visitorA = await fp.getFingerprint();

// Session B (user opened browser in a different window size)
const visitorB = await fp.getFingerprint();

const isSame = fp.compare(visitorA, visitorB);
console.log(isSame); // true (Hardware & Software matched, Visual changed)
```

### 3. Custom Weighting
Assign importance to hardware, software, and visual components:

```javascript
const fp = new Fingerprint({
  customWeights: {
    hardware: 0.7,  // Prioritize stable HW
    software: 0.2,
    visual: 0.1
  }
});
```

### 4. Fast Mode (Lower Latency)
Skip heavy timing and graphic signals for quicker execution:

```javascript
const result = await getFingerprint({ accuracy: 'fast' });
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
whouser/
├── src/
│   ├── utils/
│   │   └── helpers.js            # Core utilities (hashing, normalization, browser detection)
│   ├── signals/
│   │   ├── base-signals.js       # OS, Hardware, Screen, Locale
│   │   ├── graphic-signals.js    # Canvas, WebGL, Audio, Fonts
│   │   ├── environment-signals.js# Network, AdBlocker, Inputs, Battery
│   │   └── timing-signals.js     # CPU Benchmarks, Memory, Render Performance
│   ├── fingerprint.js            # Core logic, 3-part hash builder
│   └── index.js                  # Public API entry point
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Configuration Options

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `accuracy` | `string` | `'balanced'` | Levels: `'fast'`, `'balanced'`, `'high'`. |
| `enableBase` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable OS/Hardware signals. |
| `enableGraphic` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable Canvas/WebGL/Audio signals. |
| `enableEnvironment` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable Network/Input/AdBlock signals. |
| `enableTiming` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable CPU/Memory benchmarks. |
| `fuzzyThreshold` | `number` | `0.7` | Similarity score (0 to 1) required to consider two hashes a match. |
| `customWeights` | `object` | `null` | Override `hardware`, `software`, `visual` weights. |

---

## 🌐 Browser Support

Whouser uses modern Web APIs. It supports all **major modern browsers**:

- ✅ Google Chrome 80+
- ✅ Mozilla Firefox 75+
- ✅ Safari 14+
- ✅ Microsoft Edge 80+
- ⚠️ *Note: Safari restricts some WebGL and Audio signals; accuracy may drop slightly on macOS/iOS devices.*

---

## 🔒 Privacy & Legal Disclaimer

**Whouser** is designed for legitimate use cases such as fraud prevention, session restoration, and user preference retention without intrusive tracking.

- **GDPR/CCPA Compliance**: If you are using this in production, you **must** inform your users about the use of device fingerprinting and obtain necessary consent.
- **No Data Storage**: This library only generates a hash on the client side. It does not send any data to external servers by default. You are responsible for how you store and process the generated hash.

